South Africa’s Shoprite’s retail unit said on Thursday it would oppose the competition commission’s decision to charge it for anti-competitive behaviour. Read: Shoprite faces hefty fine for anti-competitive behaviour The Competition Commission recommended to the country’s Competition Tribunal that Shoprite Checkers be fined 10% of its turnover for the behaviour. Computicket, its event ticket selling subsidiary, was also charged and fined the same amount as its retail unit.